comment_text: I am writing as a concerned citizen to oppose the use of harmful pesticides that could damage our local water supply and harm wildlife in our community.

On behalf of the American Chemical Industry Association, we submit these technical comments regarding the proposed triazine regulations. Our members have conducted extensive research showing these compounds are safe when used according to label instructions.

As a professor of environmental toxicology at State University, I have studied triazine compounds for over 20 years. The proposed regulations align with current scientific understanding of these pesticides' environmental impact.
This comment is submitted by Political Solutions LLC on behalf of our client. We strongly support maintaining current pesticide regulations to protect American agricultural competitiveness.
I flew last week and the airplane bathroom was too small for my wheelchair. Please require larger bathrooms on all planes.
Boeing Company submits these comments in response to the proposed accessible lavatory requirements. We have analyzed the engineering and cost implications for single-aisle aircraft modifications.
I run a small regional airline and I'm worried about the costs of retrofitting our fleet, but I understand the importance of accessibility for all passengers.
